article.description: LeMonte Booker ran for three touchdowns and caught another to lead Indiana State to a 52-17 victory over Butler on Saturday in a game delayed for more than an hour due to lightning.
article.headline: Booker, Adam lead Indiana State over Butler 52-17
article.linkText: Booker, Adam lead Indiana State over Butler 52-17
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- LeMonte Booker ran for three touchdowns and caught another to lead Indiana State to a 52-17 victory over Butler on Saturday in a game delayed for more than an hour due to lightning. Booker had first-half scoring runs of 2 and 76 yards, and added a 25-yard touchdown run in the third quarter. Booker had 137 yards rushing on 11 carries. Matt Adam threw a 24-yard touchdown pass to Booker, and ran for a 37-yard score to help the Sycamores build a 31-7 lead before play was stopped with 3:43 remaining in the second quarter. Adam added a 53-yard touchdown pass to Gary Owens in the third quarter. Butler's Matt Shiltz threw a 3-yard touchdown pass to Marquese Martin-Hayes in the second quarter. Shiltz also had a 75-yard touchdown run with 2:33 to play.
